        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:28PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vale, or 16 miles west of Ontario, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Vale around 530 PM MDT.
Ontario, Payette, and Fruitland around 550 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
